hey announced in Algeria in September. But their hard work might be undermined by the countries exempted from the deal: Libya and Nigeria. Much of the 1.166-million barrels a day of agreed cuts could be offset by increases from these two countries &mdash; at least, if things go as their governments hope.Africa Is OPEC's Biggest Danger